Problem Statement Document 
Problem Title 
Medication Reminder and Adherence Problem 
Problem Description 
Many people forget to take their medicine on time or take it in wrong way. This usually happens because they have busy life or the schedule is too confusing. Some people take many medicines at different times which make it more hard to manage. Because of this, their health condition can get worse and treatment may not work properly. 
Target Users 
People with long-term illness (like diabetes or blood pressure)  
Old people who take many medicines  
Busy people who forget their medication time  
Caregivers who help patients  
Current Solutions 
Phone alarms and reminder apps  
Writing notes or using pill boxes  
Some health apps with basic reminder  
Why Current Solutions Fail 
Not easy to use for everyone, specially older people  
Cannot handle complex medicine schedule properly  
No proper tracking if medicine is taken or missed  
Reminders can be ignored easily  
Not designed specially for healthcare use  
Proposed Solution 
We will create a web application which helps users to manage their medicine better. The system will allow users to add medicines, set time and dosage, and get reminder notification. Users can also mark if they taken or missed the medicine. It will also show daily schedule in dashboard so it is easy to understand. 
The main goal is to make it simple and useful so people can follow their medication properly. 
